{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775848366025,"sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","part":{"id":"prt_d78cf9fc6001uO4kDCydFw104p","messageID":"msg_d78cf922d001LygBqpD2b8LVxe","sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848373031,"sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","part":{"id":"prt_d78cfad54001oTZcCNeIquELHa","messageID":"msg_d78cf922d001LygBqpD2b8LVxe","sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Sandbox Orchestration Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Orchestrate agent sandboxes via Kubernetes CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), a Gin HTTP API (workload manager), session persistence, garbage collection, and optional service-account authentication.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime CRD schema and API registration\n9: The system SHALL expose a namespaced `AgentRuntime` custom resource in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, with subresource `status`, print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`, and SHALL register list kind `AgentRuntimeList`.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Group version and resource naming\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API client resolving the CRD\n13: - **WHEN** the group, version, and kind are read from type metadata\n14: - **THEN** `GroupVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, kind `AgentRuntime`, and GVR resource name is `agentruntimes`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime spec fields and kubebuilder rules\n17: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with: `Ports` as `[]TargetPort` serialized under JSON key `targetPort`; required `Template` (`*SandboxTemplate`) under JSON key `podTemplate`; required `SessionTimeout` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `sessionTimeout` with kubebuilder default `\"15m\"`; required `MaxSessionDuration` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `maxSessionDuration` with kubebuilder default `\"8h\"`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: SandboxTemplate embeds Pod spec\n20: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `spec.podTemplate`\n21: - **WHEN** the template is deserialized\n22: - **THEN** `labels` and `annotations` are optional maps and `spec` is required and of type `corev1.PodSpec`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime status\n25: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` with optional `conditions` of type `[]metav1.Condition`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Conditions optional\n28: - **GIVEN** a minimal `AgentRuntime` object\n29: - **WHEN** status is omitted or empty\n30: - **THEN** deserialization succeeds without requiring `conditions`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter CRD schema\n33: The system SHALL expose a namespaced `CodeInterpreter` CRD in the same API group/version with subresource `status` and print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter GVR\n36: - **GIVEN** dynamic client configuration for workload templates\n37: - **WHEN** GVR is constructed for `codeinterpreters`\n38: - **THEN** group is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, resource `codeinterpreters`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec fields\n41: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` with: optional `Ports` (`[]TargetPort`, JSON `ports`); required `Template` (`*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`, JSON `template`); optional `SessionTimeout` with default `\"15m\"`; optional `MaxSessionDuration` with default `\"8h\"`; optional `WarmPoolSize` (`*int32`); optional `AuthMode` (`AuthModeType`, JSON `authMode`) with default `\"picod\"` and enum `picod` or `none`.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Auth mode constants\n44: - **GIVEN** API constants for auth mode\n45: - **WHEN** `AuthMode` is compared\n46: - **THEN** `AuthModePicoD` equals `\"picod\"` and `AuthModeNone` equals `\"none\"`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStatus fields\n49: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` with optional `conditions` and optional boolean `ready`.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Ready flag\n52: - **GIVEN** a reconciled `CodeInterpreter`\n53: - **WHEN** status is updated by the controller\n54: - **THEN** `status.ready` may be set to `true` alongside a `Ready` condition\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: TargetPort and Protocol types\n57: The system SHALL define `TargetPort` with optional `pathPrefix`, optional `name`, required `port` (`uint32`), and required `protocol` (`ProtocolType`) with kubebuilder default `HTTP` and enum `HTTP` or `HTTPS`.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Protocol constants\n60: - **GIVEN** port configuration without explicit protocol in some code paths\n61: - **WHEN** defaults apply at API level\n62: - **THEN** default protocol is `HTTP` per kubebuilder marker\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Workload manager health endpoint\n65: The system SHALL serve `GET /health` without authentication and SHALL respond `200` with JSON body `{\"status\":\"healthy\"}`.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Health bypasses auth middleware\n68: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth` is true\n69: - **WHEN** a client calls `GET /health` with no `Authorization` header\n70: - **THEN** the response status is 200 and body contains `\"status\":\"healthy\"`\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Workload manager v1 routes and middleware\n73: The system SHALL mount a `/v1` route group with `loggingMiddleware` then `authMiddleware` (order preserved), and SHALL register `POST /v1/agent-runtime`, `DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId`, `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, and `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId`.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Session id path parameter\n76: - **GIVEN** a delete request\n77: - **WHEN** Gin binds the path\n78: - **THEN** the session identifier is read from parameter name `sessionId` (camelCase)\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Create sandbox request validation\n81: The system SHALL accept JSON for create endpoints matching `CreateSandboxRequest` with fields `kind`, `name`, `namespace`; SHALL overwrite `kind` from the handler (`AgentRuntime` or `CodeInterpreter`); and SHALL reject requests where `kind` is not one of those, `namespace` is empty, or `name` is empty.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Validation failure returns 400\n84: - **GIVEN** the handler sets `sandboxReq.Kind` from the route and `Validate()` is called\n85: - **WHEN** `namespace` or `name` is empty in the JSON body\n86: - **THEN** the response is 400 and the error message includes `required` (e.g. `namespace is required` or `name is required`)\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Create sandbox success response\n89: On successful creation the system SHALL respond `200` with `CreateSandboxResponse` containing `sessionId`, `sandboxId`, `sandboxName`, and `entryPoints` (each entry point has `path`, `protocol`, `endpoint`).\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Entry points reflect TargetPort and pod IP\n92: - **GIVEN** a sandbox reaches running state and pod IP is resolved\n93: - **WHEN** the response is built\n94: - **THEN** each entry point `endpoint` is `host:port` joined from pod IP and configured port, with protocol string from `TargetPort.Protocol`\n95: \n96: ### Requirement: Create sandbox error responses\n97: The system SHALL return `400` with `{\"message\":...}` for invalid JSON or validation failure; `404` with message from wrapped not-found errors when AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter is missing from informer cache; `401` with message from client extraction error when `EnableAuth` is true; `500` with `{\"message\":\"internal server error\"}` for other create failures including timeout.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: JSON parse failure\n100: - **GIVEN** a non-JSON body to `POST /v1/agent-runtime`\n101: - **WHEN** the handler binds JSON\n102: - **THEN** status is 400 and message is `Invalid request body`\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Optional Bearer authentication via TokenReview\n105: When `EnableAuth` is true, the system SHALL require header `Authorization: Bearer <token>` with exactly two space-separated fields; SHALL validate via `authentication/v1` `TokenReview` create; SHALL cache results in an LRU cache (capacity 1000, entry TTL 5 minutes); and SHALL store in context: token, full username, service account name, namespace parsed from `system:serviceaccount:<ns>:<name>`.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Missing header\n108: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth` is true\n109: - **WHEN** `/v1/...` is called without `Authorization`\n110: - **THEN** response is 401 with message `Missing authorization header` and handler chain aborts\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: TokenReview success path\n113: - **GIVEN** a valid service account token and `EnableAuth` true\n114: - **WHEN** `validateServiceAccountToken` runs with cache miss\n115: - **THEN** the server creates `TokenReview` with `spec.token` set and uses `status.user.username` when `status.authenticated` is true\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: Authenticated Kubernetes operations use user client\n118: When `EnableAuth` is true, the system SHALL use a per-user dynamic client (from bearer token) for creating/deleting `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` resources; when false, SHALL use the manager’s in-cluster/default dynamic client.\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: User client cache key\n121: - **GIVEN** repeated requests from the same namespace and service account name\n122: - **WHEN** `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient` is used\n123: - **THEN** the cache key is `<namespace>:<serviceAccountName>`\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: Sandbox creation ordering and store placeholder\n126: The system SHALL call `StoreSandbox` with a placeholder `SandboxInfo` before creating the `Sandbox` or `SandboxClaim` in the API; SHALL register a one-shot watcher before create; SHALL wait up to 2 minutes for sandbox status `running` from the reconciler; SHALL resolve pod IP and then `UpdateSandbox` with full info; and SHALL roll back the created CR on failure after the wait (delete Sandbox or SandboxClaim within a 30s timeout context).\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Watcher registration before create\n129: - **GIVEN** a create request reaches `createSandbox`\n130: - **WHEN** the Sandbox CR is created\n131: - **THEN** `WatchSandboxOnce` was already invoked for that namespace/name\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Timeout returns error\n134: - **GIVEN** no running notification within 2 minutes\n135: - **WHEN** the select completes\n136: - **THEN** creation fails with error `sandbox creation timed out` and HTTP 500 is returned to the client\n137: \n138: ### Requirement: Pod IP resolution\n139: The system SHALL prefer pod name equal to sandbox name; if annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` exists on the created Sandbox (from agent-sandbox controller), SHALL use that as pod name; SHALL load pod from informer cache and require `PodRunning` and non-empty `PodIP`; otherwise SHALL list pods by label `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name=<sandboxName>` and pick the pod whose controller owner reference is kind `Sandbox` and name matches.\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Pod not running yields error\n142: - **GIVEN** a matching pod in non-Running phase\n143: - **WHEN** IP is resolved\n144: - **THEN** resolution fails with an error indicating the pod is not running\n145: \n146: ### Requirement: Delete sandbox by session\n147: The system SHALL load session from store by `sessionId`; on `ErrNotFound` return `404` with message `Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted`; delete `SandboxClaim` when stored `Kind` is `SandboxClaim`, else delete `Sandbox`; treat API `NotFound` on delete as success; then `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`; success response `200` `{\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}`.\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Store miss\n150: - **GIVEN** no session key in store\n151: - **WHEN** DELETE is invoked\n152: - **THEN** HTTP status is 404 and message mentions the session id\n153: \n154: ### Requirement: Garbage collection loop\n155: The system SHALL run a background goroutine tick every 15 seconds; each tick SHALL use a context timeout of 2 minutes; SHALL query inactive sessions with cutoff `now - 15m` and batch limit 16; SHALL query expired sessions with `before = now` and batch limit 16; SHALL merge lists and delete each unique workload then remove store entry by session ID.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: GC uses DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout\n158: - **GIVEN** GC lists inactive sandboxes\n159: - **WHEN** computing the inactive cutoff\n160: - **THEN** `inactiveTime` equals `time.Now().Add(-DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout)` where `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` is 15 minutes\n161: \n162: ### Requirement: HTTP server and process behavior\n163: The system SHALL use Gin with `gin.New()` for the workload API; SHALL serve with `h2c` wrapping and `http2.Server`; SHALL use `ReadTimeout` 15s and `IdleTimeout` 90s for HTTP when not using TLS; SHALL ping the store before listening; SHALL sync informers (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Pod) with up to 1 minute wait; on SIGINT/SIGTERM SHALL shutdown HTTP within 15s, cancel context, wait for background workers, then `Close()` the store.\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: TLS requires cert and key\n166: - **GIVEN** `EnableTLS` is true and cert or key path is empty\n167: - **WHEN** `Start` runs\n168: - **THEN** it returns an error that TLS is enabled but cert/key not provided\n169: \n170: ### Requirement: API error helper constants\n171: The system SHALL define in package `api` the sentinel errors `ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound`, `ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound`, `ErrTemplateMissing`, `ErrPublicKeyMissing`, and SHALL map `CodeInterpreter` kind to group-resource `agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters` and default kinds to `agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes` for `NewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError`.\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Session not found uses API machinery\n174: - **GIVEN** `NewSessionNotFoundError(\"sid\")`\n175: - **WHEN** the error is inspected as `APIStatus`\n176: - **THEN** the group resource is `agentcube.volcano.sh, Resource=sessions` and name is the session id\n\n(End of file - total 176 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Sandbox Orchestration Specification\n\n## Purpose\nOrchestrate agent sandboxes via Kubernetes CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), a Gin HTTP API (workload manager), session persistence, garbage collection, and optional service-account authentication.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime CRD schema and API registration\nThe system SHALL expose a namespaced `AgentRuntime` custom resource in API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, with subresource `status`, print column `Age` from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`, and SHALL register list kind `AgentRuntimeList`.\n\n#### Scenario: Group version and resource naming\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API client resolving the CRD\n- **WHEN** the group, version, and kind are read from type metadata\n- **THEN** `GroupVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`, kind `AgentRuntime`, and GVR resource name is `agentruntimes`\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime spec fields and kubebuilder rules\nThe system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with: `Ports` as `[]TargetPort` serialized under JSON key `targetPort`; required `Template` (`*SandboxTemplate`) under JSON key `podTemplate`; required `SessionTimeout` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `sessionTimeout` with kubebuilder default `\"15m\"`; required `MaxSessionDuration` (`*metav1.Duration`) under `maxSessionDuration` with kubebuilder default `\"8h\"`.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxTemplate embeds Pod spec\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `spec.podTemplate`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md","time":{"start":1775848373008,"end":1775848373028}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848373033,"sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","part":{"id":"prt_d78cfb46a001MnwDTBE2q9gRVR","messageID":"msg_d78cf922d001LygBqpD2b8LVxe","sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Idle Cleanup Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Run a controller that deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when an idle-timeout annotation indicates the sandbox has been inactive beyond a fixed grace period.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Reconciliation trigger\n9: The system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager’s API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n12: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n13: - **WHEN** the manager is running\n14: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object’s namespace and name\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Idle detection input\n17: The system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue (unless other logic applies—none in this controller).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n20: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` without `last-activity-time`\n21: - **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n22: - **THEN** the sandbox is not deleted and result has zero `RequeueAfter`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Idle detection parsing\n25: When the annotation is non-empty, the system SHALL parse it with `time.RFC3339`. On parse error, the system SHALL return `RequeueAfter: 30 seconds` and the parse error.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Invalid timestamp requeues\n28: - **GIVEN** annotation value is not RFC3339\n29: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` fails\n30: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Expiration threshold\n33: The system SHALL define `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`. The system SHALL compute `expirationTime = lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`. When `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`, the system SHALL delete the `Sandbox` resource.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Idle beyond 15 minutes triggers delete\n36: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to a time more than 15 minutes in the past\n37: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n38: - **THEN** the controller calls delete on the `Sandbox` client object\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Not yet expired requeues until expiration\n41: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is recent enough that expiration is in the future\n42: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n43: - **THEN** the result is `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)` and no delete occurs\n44: \n45: ### Requirement: Delete idempotency\n46: When delete returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL treat it as success and SHALL return empty result with nil error. Other delete errors SHALL be returned to trigger retry.\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Already deleted sandbox\n49: - **GIVEN** the API server returns not found on delete\n50: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n51: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Get not found\n54: When get returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL return empty result and nil error.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Sandbox removed before reconcile\n57: - **GIVEN** the sandbox no longer exists\n58: - **WHEN** `Get` fails with not found\n59: - **THEN** reconcile returns without error\n60: \n61: ## Requirements (binary / operator)\n62: \n63: ### Requirement: Manager options\n64: The `agentd` binary SHALL construct controller-runtime `Manager` with scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `sandboxv1alpha1` from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`, SHALL disable metrics server (`BindAddress: \"0\"`), and SHALL disable health probe server (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`).\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Signal-driven shutdown\n67: - **GIVEN** the process runs `mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())`\n68: - **WHEN** SIGTERM/SIGINT is received\n69: - **THEN** the manager stops gracefully per controller-runtime defaults\n\n(End of file - total 69 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Idle Cleanup Specification\n\n## Purpose\nRun a controller that deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when an idle-timeout annotation indicates the sandbox has been inactive beyond a fixed grace period.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Reconciliation trigger\nThe system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager’s API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n- **WHEN** the manager is running\n- **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object’s namespace and name\n\n### Requirement: Idle detection input\nThe system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue (unless other logic applies—none in this controller).\n\n#### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` without `last-activity-time`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md","time":{"start":1775848373011,"end":1775848373031}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848373040,"sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","part":{"id":"prt_d78cfa5be001egKH9bGMZCmjNd","messageID":"msg_d78cf922d001LygBqpD2b8LVxe","sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package v1alpha1\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n21: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n22: )\n23: \n24: // AgentRuntimePhase represents the current phase of an AgentRuntime.\n25: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Running;Succeeded;Failed;Unknown\n26: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n27: type AgentRuntimePhase string\n28: \n29: const (\n30: \t// AgentRuntimePhasePending indicates the sandbox is being created.\n31: \tAgentRuntimePhasePending AgentRuntimePhase = \"Pending\"\n32: \n33: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseRunning indicates the sandbox is active and running.\n34: \tAgentRuntimePhaseRunning AgentRuntimePhase = \"Running\"\n35: \n36: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseSucceeded indicates the sandbox completed successfully.\n37: \tAgentRuntimePhaseSucceeded AgentRuntimePhase = \"Succeeded\"\n38: \n39: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseFailed indicates the sandbox failed.\n40: \tAgentRuntimePhaseFailed AgentRuntimePhase = \"Failed\"\n41: \n42: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseUnknown indicates the sandbox state is unknown.\n43: \tAgentRuntimePhaseUnknown AgentRuntimePhase = \"Unknown\"\n44: )\n45: \n46: // AgentRuntimeConditionType represents a condition type for AgentRuntime.\n47: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Ready;SandboxCreated;SandboxReady;Failed\n48: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n49: type AgentRuntimeConditionType string\n50: \n51: const (\n52: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionReady indicates the AgentRuntime is ready to accept requests.\n53: \tAgentRuntimeConditionReady AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"Ready\"\n54: \n55: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox has been created.\n56: \tAgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"SandboxCreated\"\n57: \n58: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionSandboxReady indicates the sandbox is ready for use.\n59: \tAgentRuntimeConditionSandboxReady AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"SandboxReady\"\n60: \n61: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionFailed indicates the AgentRuntime has failed.\n62: \tAgentRuntimeConditionFailed AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"Failed\"\n63: )\n64: \n65: // AgentRuntimeSpec defines the desired state of AgentRuntime.\n66: // This specification describes the configuration for a sandbox instance\n67: // that will run an AI agent.\n68: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n69: \t// Image is the container image to use for the sandbox.\n70: \t// This field is required and must be a valid container image reference.\n71: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n72: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n73: \tImage string `json:\"image\"`\n74: \n75: \t// Resources defines the compute resources (CPU, memory) for the sandbox.\n76: \t// If not specified, default resource limits will be applied.\n77: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n78: \tResources *corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n79: \n80: \t// Env defines environment variables to set in the sandbox container.\n81: \t// These variables will be available to the running agent.\n82: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n83: \t// +listType=map\n84: \t// +listMapKey=name\n85: \tEnv []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n86: \n87: \t// Command overrides the default container entrypoint.\n88: \t// If not specified, the image's default entrypoint will be used.\n89: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n90: \tCommand []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n91: \n92: \t// Args provides arguments to the command or the default entrypoint.\n93: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n94: \tArgs []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n95: \n96: \t// WorkingDir specifies the working directory for the container.\n97: \t// If not specified, the container's default working directory will be used.\n98: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n99: \tWorkingDir string `json:\"workingDir,omitempty\"`\n100: \n101: \t// Ports defines the ports to expose from the sandbox container.\n102: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n103: \t// +listType=map\n104: \t// +listMapKey=containerPort\n105: \tPorts []corev1.ContainerPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n106: \n107: \t// VolumeMounts defines volumes to mount into the sandbox container.\n108: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n109: \t// +listType=map\n110: \t// +listMapKey=name\n111: \tVolumeMounts []corev1.VolumeMount `json:\"volumeMounts,omitempty\"`\n112: \n113: \t// Volumes defines the volumes that can be mounted by the sandbox.\n114: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n115: \t// +listType=map\n116: \t// +listMapKey=name\n117: \tVolumes []corev1.Volume `json:\"volumes,omitempty\"`\n118: \n119: \t// ServiceAccountName specifies the service account to use for the sandbox pod.\n120: \t// If not specified, the default service account will be used.\n121: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n122: \tServiceAccountName string `json:\"serviceAccountName,omitempty\"`\n123: \n124: \t// NodeSelector specifies node labels for pod scheduling.\n125: \t// The pod will only be scheduled on nodes matching these labels.\n126: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n127: \t// +mapType=atomic\n128: \tNodeSelector map[string]string `json:\"nodeSelector,omitempty\"`\n129: \n130: \t// Tolerations allow the pod to be scheduled on nodes with matching taints.\n131: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n132: \t// +listType=atomic\n133: \tTolerations []corev1.Toleration `json:\"tolerations,omitempty\"`\n134: \n135: \t// Affinity defines the scheduling constraints for the pod.\n136: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n137: \tAffinity *corev1.Affinity `json:\"affinity,omitempty\"`\n138: \n139: \t// TTLSecondsAfterFinished specifies the time to live (in seconds) after\n140: \t// the sandbox has finished (succeeded or failed). The sandbox will be\n141: \t// automatically deleted after this time.\n142: \t// If not specified, the sandbox will not be automatically deleted.\n143: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n144: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n145: \tTTLSecondsAfterFinished *int32 `json:\"ttlSecondsAfterFinished,omitempty\"`\n146: \n147: \t// IdleTimeoutSeconds specifies the maximum time (in seconds) the sandbox\n148: \t// can be idle before being terminated. If not specified, no idle timeout\n149: \t// is enforced.\n150: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n151: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n152: \tIdleTimeoutSeconds *int32 `json:\"idleTimeoutSeconds,omitempty\"`\n153: \n154: \t// MaxLifetimeSeconds specifies the maximum lifetime (in seconds) of the sandbox.\n155: \t// The sandbox will be terminated after this duration regardless of activity.\n156: \t// If not specified, no maximum lifetime is enforced.\n157: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n158: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n159: \tMaxLifetimeSeconds *int32 `json:\"maxLifetimeSeconds,omitempty\"`\n160: }\n161: \n162: // AgentRuntimeStatus defines the observed state of AgentRuntime.\n163: // This status is updated by the controller to reflect the current\n164: // state of the sandbox instance.\n165: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n166: \t// Phase represents the current phase of the AgentRuntime.\n167: \t// Possible values: Pending, Running, Succeeded, Failed, Unknown.\n168: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n169: \tPhase AgentRuntimePhase `json:\"phase,omitempty\"`\n170: \n171: \t// Conditions represents the latest available observations of the AgentRuntime's state.\n172: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n173: \t// +listType=map\n174: \t// +listMapKey=type\n175: \t// +patchMergeKey=type\n176: \t// +patchStrategy=merge\n177: \tConditions []AgentRuntimeCondition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n178: \n179: \t// SandboxID is the unique identifier of the created sandbox pod.\n180: \t// This is set once the sandbox pod has been successfully created.\n181: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n182: \tSandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId,omitempty\"`\n183: \n184: \t// PodName is the name of the pod running the sandbox.\n185: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n186: \tPodName string `json:\"podName,omitempty\"`\n187: \n188: \t// PodIP is the IP address assigned to the sandbox pod.\n189: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n190: \tPodIP string `json:\"podIP,omitempty\"`\n191: \n192: \t// StartTime is the time when the sandbox was started.\n193: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n194: \tStartTime *metav1.Time `json:\"startTime,omitempty\"`\n195: \n196: \t// CompletionTime is the time when the sandbox completed (succeeded or failed).\n197: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n198: \tCompletionTime *metav1.Time `json:\"completionTime,omitempty\"`\n199: \n200: \t// LastActivityTime is the time of the last activity in the sandbox.\n201: \t// Used for idle timeout tracking.\n202: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n203: \tLastActivityTime *metav1.Time `json:\"lastActivityTime,omitempty\"`\n204: \n205: \t// Message provides a human-readable description of the current status.\n206: \t// This may contain error messages or other status information.\n207: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n208: \tMessage string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n209: \n210: \t// Reason provides a brief reason for the current phase.\n211: \t// This is typically a CamelCase string indicating why the phase is set.\n212: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n213: \tReason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n214: \n215: \t// ObservedGeneration is the most recent generation observed by the controller.\n216: \t// This is used to determine if the spec has been processed.\n217: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n218: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n219: \tObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n220: }\n221: \n222: // AgentRuntimeCondition represents a condition of an AgentRuntime.\n223: type AgentRuntimeCondition struct {\n224: \t// Type is the type of the condition.\n225: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n226: \tType AgentRuntimeConditionType `json:\"type\"`\n227: \n228: \t// Status is the status of the condition (True, False, Unknown).\n229: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n230: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=True;False;Unknown\n231: \tStatus corev1.ConditionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n232: \n233: \t// LastTransitionTime is the last time the condition transitioned.\n234: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n235: \tLastTransitionTime metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime,omitempty\"`\n236: \n237: \t// Reason is a brief reason for the condition's last transition.\n238: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n239: \tReason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n240: \n241: \t// Message is a human-readable message indicating details about the transition.\n242: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n243: \tMessage string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n244: }\n245: \n246: // +genclient\n247: // +genclient:noStatus\n248: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n249: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n250: // +kubebuilder:resource:path=agentruntimes,shortName=ar;ars,singular=agentruntime,categories={agentcube,all}\n251: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n252: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Phase\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.phase`,description=\"Current phase of the agent runtime\"\n253: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Sandbox\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.sandboxId`,description=\"ID of the sandbox pod\"\n254: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=date,JSONPath=`.metadata.creationTimestamp`,description=\"Time since creation\"\n255: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Message\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.message`,priority=1\n256: \n257: // AgentRuntime is the Schema for the agentruntimes API.\n258: // An AgentRuntime represents a sandbox instance for running AI agents.\n259: // The controller creates and manages the lifecycle of the underlying\n260: // sandbox pod based on this resource.\n261: type AgentRuntime struct {\n262: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n263: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n264: \n265: \t// Spec defines the desired state of the AgentRuntime.\n266: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n267: \tSpec AgentRuntimeSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n268: \n269: \t// Status defines the observed state of the AgentRuntime.\n270: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n271: \tStatus AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n272: }\n273: \n274: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n275: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n276: \n277: // AgentRuntimeList contains a list of AgentRuntime resources.\n278: type AgentRuntimeList struct {\n279: \tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n280: \tmetav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n281: \n282: \t// Items is the list of AgentRuntime resources.\n283: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n284: \tItems []AgentRuntime `json:\"items\"`\n285: }\n\n(End of file - total 285 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go","time":{"start":1775848373003,"end":1775848373037}}}}
