{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848661665,"sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","part":{"id":"prt_d78d22419001L5fqr8RNXWEHPc","messageID":"msg_d78d1e151001NlGGy5CBgB9Ij7","sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:18","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-006  \n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n\nImplement the Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management functionality for the WorkloadManager. This includes HTTP endpoints for deleting sandboxes (single, batch, force), graceful shutdown with configurable timeout, resource cleanup, idle detection, and orphan cleanup background workers. The implementation integrates with the existing HTTP service framework (AR-004) and extends the sandbox creation handler (AR-005).\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Sandbox Single Deletion Endpoint\n\nThe system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to delete a single sandbox by its session ID.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete existing sandbox gracefully\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-abc-123` exists in the Store\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/sess-abc-123`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL:\n  1. Extract the sessionID from the path parameter\n  2. Load the sandbox from Store by sessionID\n  3. Initiate graceful shutdown with default 30s timeout\n  4. Delete the underlying Sandbox/SandboxClaim CR via dynamic client\n  5. Delete the Store entry\n  6. Return HTTP 200 with `DeleteSandboxResponse` containing sandboxId and status \"deleted\"\n\n#### Scenario: Delete sandbox with custom graceful timeout\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-def-456` exists\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/sess-def-456?gracefulTimeout=60s`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL use 60-second graceful shutdown timeout instead of default 30s\n\n#### Scenario: Delete non-existent sandbox returns 404\n- **GIVEN** no sandbox with sessionID `sess-missing-789` exists in Store\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/sess-missing-789`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with message \"Session ID sess-missing-789 not found, maybe already deleted\"\n\n#### Scenario: Delete sandbox already being deleted returns 409\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-deleting-000` is in \"terminating\" status\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/sess-deleting-000`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 409 with error code `DELETION_IN_PROGRESS`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete CodeInterpreter sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter sandbox with sessionID `sess-ci-111` exists\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/sess-ci-111`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL delete the SandboxClaim (if warm pool) or Sandbox and return HTTP 200\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Sandbox Force Delete Endpoint\n\nThe system SHALL support force deletion that bypasses graceful shutdown.\n\n#### Scenario: Force delete sandbox immediately\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-stuck-222` exists and is stuck in terminating\n- **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/sandboxes/sess-stuck-222/terminate` or DELETE with `?force=true`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL:\n  1. Skip graceful shutdown phase\n  2. Force delete the CR with grace period 0\n  3. Immediately delete the Store entry\n  4. Return HTTP 200 with status \"force-deleted\"\n\n#### Scenario: Force delete with cascade\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with dependent resources exists\n- **WHEN** a force delete is requested with `?force=true&orphanDependents=false`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL delete all dependent resources (pods, services) before deleting the sandbox\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Sandbox Batch Deletion Endpoint\n\nThe system SHALL support batch deletion of multiple sandboxes.\n\n#### Scenario: Batch delete multiple sandboxes\n- **GIVEN** sandboxes with sessionIDs `[\"sess-1\", \"sess-2\", \"sess-3\"]` exist\n- **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/sandboxes` with body `{\"sessionIds\": [\"sess-1\", \"sess-2\", \"sess-3\"]}`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL:\n  1. Validate all session IDs\n  2. Initiate deletion for all sandboxes in parallel\n  3. Return HTTP 200 with `BatchDeleteResponse` containing:\n     - `deleted`: list of successfully deleted sandbox IDs\n     - `failed`: list of failed deletions with error details\n     - `notFound`: list of session IDs not found\n\n#### Scenario: Batch delete with partial failure\n- **GIVEN** sessionIDs `[\"sess-exists\", \"sess-missing\", \"sess-error\"]` where \"sess-missing\" doesn't exist and \"sess-error\" fails to delete\n- **WHEN** a batch delete is requested\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with partial results and details for each failure\n\n#### Scenario: Batch delete with limit\n- **GIVEN** a request with more than 100 session IDs\n- **WHEN** validated\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"batch size exceeds maximum of 100\"\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Graceful Shutdown Flow\n\nThe system SHALL implement graceful shutdown with configurable timeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Graceful shutdown succeeds within timeout\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-grace-333` is running\n- **WHEN** delete is called with gracefulTimeout=30s\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Set sandbox status to \"terminating\" in Store\n  2. Send graceful shutdown signal to sandbox pod\n  3. Wait for pod to terminate or timeout\n  4. If pod terminates within 30s, mark as \"deleted\"\n  5. Return success response\n\n#### Scenario: Graceful shutdown times out\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod ignores shutdown signals\n- **WHEN** gracefulTimeout=30s elapses without pod termination\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Force delete the pod with grace period 0\n  2. Log a warning about graceful shutdown timeout\n  3. Continue with resource cleanup\n  4. Return success with status \"deleted\" and warning flag\n\n#### Scenario: Custom graceful timeout via query parameter\n- **GIVEN** a request with `?gracefulTimeout=120s`\n- **WHEN** processing the delete\n- **THEN** the system SHALL wait up to 120 seconds for graceful shutdown\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Resource Cleanup\n\nThe system SHALL clean up all resources associated with a sandbox.\n\n#### Scenario: Cleanup sandbox resources\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox has associated Pod, Service, and Ingress resources\n- **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Delete the Sandbox/SandboxClaim CR\n  2. Delete all dependent pods\n  3. Delete associated services\n  4. Delete ingress rules (if any)\n  5. Update Store entry status to \"deleted\"\n\n#### Scenario: Cleanup with owner references\n- **GIVEN** resources have owner references pointing to the Sandbox\n- **WHEN** the Sandbox CR is deleted with `propagationPolicy=Foreground`\n- **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL garbage collect all owned resources automatically\n\n#### Scenario: Store cleanup after resource deletion\n- **GIVEN** the Sandbox CR has been successfully deleted\n- **WHEN** resource cleanup completes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()` to remove the Store entry\n\n#### Scenario: Handle cleanup failure\n- **GIVEN** a resource deletion fails (e.g., API server error)\n- **WHEN** cleanup is attempted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Retry deletion up to 3 times with exponential backoff\n  2. If still failing, mark sandbox status as \"cleanup-failed\"\n  3. Return HTTP 500 with error code `CLEANUP_FAILED`\n  4. Background worker will retry cleanup later\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Lifecycle State Management\n\nThe system SHALL track and expose lifecycle states for sandboxes.\n\n#### Scenario: Get lifecycle state\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-state-444` exists\n- **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/v1/sandboxes/sess-state-444/lifecycle`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with `LifecycleStateResponse` containing:\n  - Current state (running, idle, terminating, terminated, failed)\n  - State history\n  - Last transition time\n  - Reason for current state\n\n#### Scenario: Lifecycle state transitions\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox transitions from \"running\" to \"terminating\" to \"terminated\"\n- **WHEN** state changes occur\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Update state in Store\n  2. Emit lifecycle event\n  3. Record transition timestamp and reason\n\n#### Scenario: List sandboxes by lifecycle state\n- **GIVEN** multiple sandboxes in various states\n- **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/v1/sandboxes?state=terminating`\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return only sandboxes in the \"terminating\" state\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Idle Detection Background Worker\n\nThe system SHALL run a background worker to detect and auto-delete idle sandboxes.\n\n#### Scenario: Detect idle sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `lastActivityTime` older than 15 minutes ago (configurable)\n- **WHEN** the idle detector scans (every 1 minute by default)\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Identify sandbox as idle\n  2. Check grace period (5 minutes default) has passed\n  3. Initiate automatic deletion\n  4. Emit idle timeout event\n\n#### Scenario: Activity resets idle timer\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox was marked for idle deletion\n- **WHEN** new activity updates `lastActivityTime` before deletion\n- **THEN** the system SHALL cancel the scheduled deletion and reset idle status\n\n#### Scenario: Disable idle detection\n- **GIVEN** configuration `IDLE_DETECTION_ENABLED=false`\n- **WHEN** the system starts\n- **THEN** the idle detector SHALL NOT be started\n\n#### Scenario: Configurable idle timeout\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `SANDBOX_IDLE_TIMEOUT=30m`\n- **WHEN** checking for idle sandboxes\n- **THEN** sandboxes idle for more than 30 minutes SHALL be marked for deletion\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Orphan Cleanup Background Worker\n\nThe system SHALL run a background worker to detect and clean up orphan resources.\n\n#### Scenario: Detect orphan sandbox CR\n- **GIVEN** a Sandbox CR exists without a corresponding Store entry\n- **WHEN** the orphan detector scans (every 5 minutes by default)\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Identify the CR as orphan\n  2. Check if CR is older than `ORPHAN_MAX_AGE` (1 hour default)\n  3. Delete the orphan CR\n  4. Log orphan cleanup event\n\n#### Scenario: Detect zombie Store entry\n- **GIVEN** a Store entry exists for a deleted Sandbox CR\n- **WHEN** the orphan detector scans\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Verify CR no longer exists in Kubernetes\n  2. Delete the stale Store entry\n  3. Log cleanup event\n\n#### Scenario: Handle detection errors\n- **GIVEN** the orphan detector encounters an API error\n- **WHEN** scanning for orphans\n- **THEN** the system SHALL log the error and continue with next item (not crash)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Idempotency and Concurrency\n\nThe system SHALL handle concurrent deletion requests safely.\n\n#### Scenario: Duplicate delete requests\n- **GIVEN** a delete request for sessionID `sess-dup-555` is in progress\n- **WHEN** another delete request arrives for the same sessionID\n- **THEN** the second request SHALL return HTTP 409 with `DELETION_IN_PROGRESS` error\n\n#### Scenario: Retry after in-progress deletion completes\n- **GIVEN** a previous delete request completed successfully\n- **WHEN** another delete request arrives for the same sessionID\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 (sandbox not found)\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrent batch deletes\n- **GIVEN** two batch delete requests include overlapping session IDs\n- **WHEN** both requests are processed concurrently\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Use distributed locking to prevent race conditions\n  2. Ensure each sandbox is deleted only once\n  3. Return appropriate results to both callers\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error Handling and HTTP Status Mapping\n\nThe system SHALL map internal errors to appropriate HTTP status codes.\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid session ID format\n- **GIVEN** a request with malformed session ID `sess-invalid-!!!`\n- **WHEN** the request is validated\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"invalid session ID format\"\n\n#### Scenario: Kubernetes API not found\n- **GIVEN** the Sandbox CR is not found in Kubernetes (but exists in Store)\n- **WHEN** attempting to delete\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Treat as success (CR already deleted)\n  2. Clean up the Store entry\n  3. Return HTTP 200\n\n#### Scenario: Kubernetes API conflict\n- **GIVEN** another process is modifying the Sandbox CR\n- **WHEN** attempting to delete\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Retry up to 3 times with exponential backoff\n  2. If still conflicting, return HTTP 409 with `CONFLICT` error code\n\n#### Scenario: Store unavailable\n- **GIVEN** the Store (Redis) is unreachable\n- **WHEN** attempting to load or delete sandbox info\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 503 with message \"store temporarily unavailable\"\n\n#### Scenario: Kubernetes API unauthorized\n- **GIVEN** the service account lacks delete permissions\n- **WHEN** attempting to delete Sandbox CR\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with message \"forbidden: insufficient permissions\"\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Request Validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate all deletion requests.\n\n#### Scenario: Validate single delete request\n- **GIVEN** a DELETE request to `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId`\n- **WHEN** the request is validated\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Check sessionId is not empty\n  2. Verify sessionId format (UUID or alphanumeric)\n  3. Validate optional query parameters (gracefulTimeout, force, orphanDependents)\n\n#### Scenario: Validate batch delete request\n- **GIVEN** a batch delete request with body\n- **WHEN** validated\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Check sessionIds array is present and non-empty\n  2. Verify array length <= 100\n  3. Validate each sessionId format\n  4. Check for duplicate sessionIds\n\n#### Scenario: Reject empty session ID\n- **GIVEN** a request with empty sessionId parameter\n- **WHEN** validated\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"session ID is required\"\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Authentication Integration\n\nThe system SHALL integrate with authentication middleware when enabled.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete with authentication enabled\n- **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and a valid bearer token in request\n- **WHEN** processing a delete request\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Extract service account from auth context\n  2. Use per-user K8s client via `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient()`\n  3. Verify user has RBAC permissions to delete Sandboxes in the namespace\n\n#### Scenario: Reject delete without auth\n- **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and no Authorization header\n- **WHEN** the auth middleware processes the request\n- **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 before reaching the delete handler\n\n#### Scenario: Delete with insufficient permissions\n- **GIVEN** a user with read-only access attempts to delete\n- **WHEN** the K8s delete call is made\n- **THEN** the Kubernetes API SHALL return 403 and the server SHALL propagate it\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Response Building\n\nThe system SHALL build proper deletion responses.\n\n#### Scenario: Build single delete response\n- **GIVEN** a successful deletion of sandbox with:\n  - SessionID: `sess-abc-123`\n  - SandboxID: `sandbox-xyz-789`\n  - Resources cleaned: Pod, Service\n- **WHEN** building the response\n- **THEN** the response SHALL contain:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"success\": true,\n    \"data\": {\n      \"sandboxId\": \"sandbox-xyz-789\",\n      \"sessionId\": \"sess-abc-123\",\n      \"status\": \"deleted\",\n      \"deletedAt\": \"2026-04-11T10:00:00Z\",\n      \"resourcesCleaned\": [\n        {\"kind\": \"Pod\", \"name\": \"sandbox-pod-xyz\", \"namespace\": \"default\"},\n        {\"kind\": \"Service\", \"name\": \"sandbox-svc-xyz\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}\n      ]\n    },\n    \"requestId\": \"req-uuid\",\n    \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-11T10:00:00Z\"\n  }\n  ```\n\n#### Scenario: Build batch delete response\n- **GIVEN** a batch delete with mixed results\n- **WHEN** building the response\n- **THEN** the response SHALL contain separate arrays for deleted, failed, and notFound items\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Context Propagation and Cancellation\n\nThe system SHALL properly propagate context through the deletion flow.\n\n#### Scenario: Pass context through deletion flow\n- **GIVEN** a request context with requestID and timeout\n- **WHEN** the deletion flow executes (validate → shutdown → cleanup → store delete)\n- **THEN** the context SHALL be passed to all operations for cancellation and timeout handling\n\n#### Scenario: Handle client disconnect during deletion\n- **GIVEN** a deletion is in progress\n- **WHEN** the client disconnects (context cancelled)\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Continue the deletion process (don't abort mid-way)\n  2. Log the client disconnect\n  3. Complete the cleanup\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout context for K8s operations\n- **GIVEN** a deletion involves K8s API calls\n- **WHEN** calling the dynamic client\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `context.WithTimeout()` with appropriate deadline for each operation\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL support configuration via environment variables.\n\n#### Scenario: Configure graceful timeout default\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `DEFAULT_GRACEFUL_TIMEOUT=60s`\n- **WHEN** no query parameter is provided\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use 60 seconds as default graceful timeout\n\n#### Scenario: Configure idle detection\n- **GIVEN** environment variables:\n  - `IDLE_DETECTION_ENABLED=true`\n  - `SANDBOX_IDLE_TIMEOUT=20m`\n  - `IDLE_SCAN_INTERVAL=2m`\n  - `IDLE_GRACE_PERIOD=3m`\n- **WHEN** the idle detector starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL use these values instead of defaults\n\n#### Scenario: Configure orphan detection\n- **GIVEN** environment variables:\n  - `ORPHAN_DETECTION_ENABLED=true`\n  - `ORPHAN_SCAN_INTERVAL=10m`\n  - `ORPHAN_MAX_AGE=2h`\n- **WHEN** the orphan detector starts\n- **THEN** it SHALL use these values\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/handler/delete.go` | HTTP handler for single sandbox deletion |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/handler/batch.go` | HTTP handler for batch deletion |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/handler/force.go` | HTTP handler for force deletion |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/manager/manager.go` | `LifecycleManager` interface and orchestration |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/manager/shutdown.go` | Graceful shutdown implementation |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/manager/cleanup.go` | Resource cleanup implementation |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/manager/state.go` | Lifecycle state machine |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/detector/idle.go` | Idle timeout detector worker |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/detector/orphan.go` | Orphan resource detector worker |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/types/lifecycle.go` | Lifecycle types and constants |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/server/routes.go` | Route registration for deletion endpoints |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/handler/delete_test.go` | Handler unit tests |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/manager/shutdown_test.go` | Shutdown flow tests |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/detector/idle_test.go` | Idle detector tests |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated Kubernetes clientset, informers |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Dynamic client for Sandbox CR deletion |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes API machinery, deletion options |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | Latest | HTTP framework (inherited from AR-004) |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | Latest | UUID validation |\n| `github.com/go-redis/redis/v8` | Latest | Store operations for sandbox info |\n\n---\n\n## API Endpoints Summary\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` | Delete AgentRuntime sandbox |\n| DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` | Delete CodeInterpreter sandbox |\n| DELETE | `/v1/sandboxes` | Batch delete sandboxes |\n| POST | `/v1/sandboxes/:sessionId/terminate` | Force terminate sandbox |\n| GET | `/v1/sandboxes/:sessionId/lifecycle` | Get lifecycle state |\n| GET | `/v1/sandboxes` | List sandboxes (with optional state filter) |\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n### DeleteSandboxRequest\n```go\ntype DeleteSandboxRequest struct {\n    SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n}\n```\n\n### DeleteSandboxResponse\n```go\ntype DeleteSandboxResponse struct {\n    SandboxID        string         `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SessionID        string         `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    Status           string         `json:\"status\"` // \"deleted\", \"terminating\", \"failed\"\n    DeletedAt        time.Time      `json:\"deletedAt,omitempty\"`\n    ResourcesCleaned []ResourceInfo `json:\"resourcesCleaned,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype ResourceInfo struct {\n    Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`\n    Name      string `json:\"name\"`\n    Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n}\n```\n\n### BatchDeleteRequest\n```go\ntype BatchDeleteRequest struct {\n    SessionIDs []string `json:\"sessionIds\" validate:\"required,min=1,max=100\"`\n}\n```\n\n### BatchDeleteResponse\n```go\ntype BatchDeleteResponse struct {\n    Deleted  []BatchDeleteResult `json:\"deleted\"`\n    Failed   []BatchDeleteResult `json:\"failed\"`\n    NotFound []string            `json:\"notFound\"`\n}\n\ntype BatchDeleteResult struct {\n    SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId,omitempty\"`\n    Error     string `json:\"error,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### DeleteOptions\n```go\ntype DeleteOptions struct {\n    GracefulTimeout   time.Duration             `json:\"gracefulTimeout,omitempty\" default:\"30s\"`\n    Force             bool                      `json:\"force,omitempty\" default:\"false\"`\n    OrphanDependents  bool                      `json:\"orphanDependents,omitempty\" default:\"false\"`\n    PropagationPolicy *metav1.DeletionPropagation `json:\"propagationPolicy,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### LifecycleState\n```go\ntype LifecycleState string\n\nconst (\n    StateRunning      LifecycleState = \"running\"\n    StateIdle         LifecycleState = \"idle\"\n    StateTerminating  LifecycleState = \"terminating\"\n    StateTerminated   LifecycleState = \"terminated\"\n    StateFailed       LifecycleState = \"failed\"\n)\n```\n\n### LifecycleStateResponse\n```go\ntype LifecycleStateResponse struct {\n    SessionID          string             `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxID          string             `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    CurrentState       LifecycleState     `json:\"currentState\"`\n    PreviousState      LifecycleState     `json:\"previousState,omitempty\"`\n    LastTransitionTime time.Time          `json:\"lastTransitionTime\"`\n    Reason             string             `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n    StateHistory       []StateTransition  `json:\"stateHistory,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype StateTransition struct {\n    FromState LifecycleState `json:\"fromState\"`\n    ToState   LifecycleState `json:\"toState\"`\n    Timestamp time.Time      `json:\"timestamp\"`\n    Reason    string         `json:\"reason\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Integration with client-go\n\n| Component | Usage |\n|-----------|-------|\n| `dynamic.Interface` | Delete Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs |\n| `metav1.DeleteOptions` | Configure graceful period, propagation policy |\n| `informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory` | Watch for resource changes during deletion |\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- Deletion is idempotent; deleting a non-existent sandbox returns 404, but force deleting returns 200 if already deleted\n- Graceful shutdown timeout can be customized per-request via query parameter or globally via environment variable\n- Background workers (idle detector, orphan cleaner) run independently and are resilient to individual operation failures\n- All K8s API errors are mapped to appropriate HTTP status codes following Kubernetes conventions\n- Store cleanup is attempted even if resource cleanup fails to prevent data inconsistency\n- Batch deletion processes sandboxes in parallel with a configurable concurrency limit (default: 10)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/workloadmanager/service/service.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/constants.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types/request.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types/response.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":24,"character":6},"end":{"line":24,"character":17}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":45,"character":20},"end":{"line":45,"character":31}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":75,"character":6},"end":{"line":75,"character":17}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":78,"character":8},"end":{"line":78,"character":19}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775848661652,"end":1775848661662}}}}
