{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775848668024,"sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","part":{"id":"prt_d78d43b75001NkUJU9fvg2U0Q6","messageID":"msg_d78d422e1001N6HhfHkYjiNbnn","sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848670409,"sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","part":{"id":"prt_d78d43ec4001BtWpc9pFXBiTmX","messageID":"msg_d78d422e1001N6HhfHkYjiNbnn","sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:19","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-006  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: \n10: Implement the Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management functionality for the WorkloadManager. This includes HTTP endpoints for deleting sandboxes (single, batch, force), graceful shutdown with configurable timeout, resource cleanup, idle detection, and orphan cleanup background workers. The implementation integrates with the existing HTTP service framework (AR-004) and extends the sandbox creation handler (AR-005).\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Sandbox Single Deletion Endpoint\n17: \n18: The system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to delete a single sandbox by its session ID.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Delete existing sandbox gracefully\n21: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-abc-123` exists in the Store\n22: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/sess-abc-123`\n23: - **THEN** the server SHALL:\n24:   1. Extract the sessionID from the path parameter\n25:   2. Load the sandbox from Store by sessionID\n26:   3. Initiate graceful shutdown with default 30s timeout\n27:   4. Delete the underlying Sandbox/SandboxClaim CR via dynamic client\n28:   5. Delete the Store entry\n29:   6. Return HTTP 200 with `DeleteSandboxResponse` containing sandboxId and status \"deleted\"\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox with custom graceful timeout\n32: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-def-456` exists\n33: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/sess-def-456?gracefulTimeout=60s`\n34: - **THEN** the server SHALL use 60-second graceful shutdown timeout instead of default 30s\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Delete non-existent sandbox returns 404\n37: - **GIVEN** no sandbox with sessionID `sess-missing-789` exists in Store\n38: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/sess-missing-789`\n39: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with message \"Session ID sess-missing-789 not found, maybe already deleted\"\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox already being deleted returns 409\n42: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-deleting-000` is in \"terminating\" status\n43: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/sess-deleting-000`\n44: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 409 with error code `DELETION_IN_PROGRESS`\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Delete CodeInterpreter sandbox\n47: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter sandbox with sessionID `sess-ci-111` exists\n48: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/sess-ci-111`\n49: - **THEN** the server SHALL delete the SandboxClaim (if warm pool) or Sandbox and return HTTP 200\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Sandbox Force Delete Endpoint\n54: \n55: The system SHALL support force deletion that bypasses graceful shutdown.\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Force delete sandbox immediately\n58: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with sessionID `sess-stuck-222` exists and is stuck in terminating\n59: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/sandboxes/sess-stuck-222/terminate` or DELETE with `?force=true`\n60: - **THEN** the server SHALL:\n61:   1. Skip graceful shutdown phase\n62:   2. Force delete the CR with grace period 0\n63:   3. Immediately delete the Store entry\n64:   4. Return HTTP 200 with status \"force-deleted\"\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Force delete with cascade\n67: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with dependent resources exists\n68: - **WHEN** a force delete is requested with `?force=true&orphanDependents=false`\n69: - **THEN** the server SHALL delete all dependent resources (pods, services) before deleting the sandbox\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ### Requirement: Sandbox Batch Deletion Endpoint\n74: \n75: The system SHALL support batch deletion of multiple sandboxes.\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: Batch delete multiple sandboxes\n78: - **GIVEN** sandboxes with sessionIDs `[\"sess-1\", \"sess-2\", \"sess-3\"]` exist\n79: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/v1/sandboxes` with body `{\"sessionIds\": [\"sess-1\", \"sess-2\", \"sess-3\"]}`\n80: - **THEN** the server SHALL:\n81:   1. Validate all session IDs\n82:   2. Initiate deletion for all sandboxes in parallel\n83:   3. Return HTTP 200 with `BatchDeleteResponse` containing:\n84:      - `deleted`: list of successfully deleted sandbox IDs\n85:      - `failed`: list of failed deletions with error details\n86:      - `notFound`: list of session IDs not found\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Batch delete with partial failure\n89: - **GIVEN** sessionIDs `[\"sess-exists\", \"sess-missing\", \"sess-error\"]` where \"sess-missing\" doesn't exist and \"sess-error\" fails to delete\n90: - **WHEN** a batch delete is requested\n91: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with partial results and details for each failure\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Batch delete with limit\n94: - **GIVEN** a request with more than 100 session IDs\n95: - **WHEN** validated\n96: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"batch size exceeds maximum of 100\"\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ### Requirement: Graceful Shutdown Flow\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 608. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-006  \n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n\nImplement the Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management functionality for the WorkloadManager. This includes HTTP endpoints for deleting sandboxes (single, batch, force), graceful shutdown with configurable timeout, resource cleanup, idle detection, and orphan cleanup background workers. The implementation integrates with the existing HTTP service framework (AR-004) and extends the sandbox creation handler (AR-005).\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Sandbox Single Deletion Endpoint\n\nThe system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to delete a single sandbox by its session ID.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete existing sandbox gracefully","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775848670397,"end":1775848670406}}}}
