{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848674652,"sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","part":{"id":"prt_d78d44f94001qXnzVQxNeJPx10","messageID":"msg_d78d444fa001xOU9pygNeY79x0","sessionID":"ses_28730ac95ffeAn455E0f48zV8R","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:20","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","offset":500,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n500: ### DeleteSandboxRequest\n501: ```go\n502: type DeleteSandboxRequest struct {\n503:     SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n504: }\n505: ```\n506: \n507: ### DeleteSandboxResponse\n508: ```go\n509: type DeleteSandboxResponse struct {\n510:     SandboxID        string         `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n511:     SessionID        string         `json:\"sessionId\"`\n512:     Status           string         `json:\"status\"` // \"deleted\", \"terminating\", \"failed\"\n513:     DeletedAt        time.Time      `json:\"deletedAt,omitempty\"`\n514:     ResourcesCleaned []ResourceInfo `json:\"resourcesCleaned,omitempty\"`\n515: }\n516: \n517: type ResourceInfo struct {\n518:     Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`\n519:     Name      string `json:\"name\"`\n520:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n521: }\n522: ```\n523: \n524: ### BatchDeleteRequest\n525: ```go\n526: type BatchDeleteRequest struct {\n527:     SessionIDs []string `json:\"sessionIds\" validate:\"required,min=1,max=100\"`\n528: }\n529: ```\n530: \n531: ### BatchDeleteResponse\n532: ```go\n533: type BatchDeleteResponse struct {\n534:     Deleted  []BatchDeleteResult `json:\"deleted\"`\n535:     Failed   []BatchDeleteResult `json:\"failed\"`\n536:     NotFound []string            `json:\"notFound\"`\n537: }\n538: \n539: type BatchDeleteResult struct {\n540:     SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n541:     SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId,omitempty\"`\n542:     Error     string `json:\"error,omitempty\"`\n543: }\n544: ```\n545: \n546: ### DeleteOptions\n547: ```go\n548: type DeleteOptions struct {\n549:     GracefulTimeout   time.Duration             `json:\"gracefulTimeout,omitempty\" default:\"30s\"`\n550:     Force             bool                      `json:\"force,omitempty\" default:\"false\"`\n551:     OrphanDependents  bool                      `json:\"orphanDependents,omitempty\" default:\"false\"`\n552:     PropagationPolicy *metav1.DeletionPropagation `json:\"propagationPolicy,omitempty\"`\n553: }\n554: ```\n555: \n556: ### LifecycleState\n557: ```go\n558: type LifecycleState string\n559: \n560: const (\n561:     StateRunning      LifecycleState = \"running\"\n562:     StateIdle         LifecycleState = \"idle\"\n563:     StateTerminating  LifecycleState = \"terminating\"\n564:     StateTerminated   LifecycleState = \"terminated\"\n565:     StateFailed       LifecycleState = \"failed\"\n566: )\n567: ```\n568: \n569: ### LifecycleStateResponse\n570: ```go\n571: type LifecycleStateResponse struct {\n572:     SessionID          string             `json:\"sessionId\"`\n573:     SandboxID          string             `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n574:     CurrentState       LifecycleState     `json:\"currentState\"`\n575:     PreviousState      LifecycleState     `json:\"previousState,omitempty\"`\n576:     LastTransitionTime time.Time          `json:\"lastTransitionTime\"`\n577:     Reason             string             `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n578:     StateHistory       []StateTransition  `json:\"stateHistory,omitempty\"`\n579: }\n580: \n581: type StateTransition struct {\n582:     FromState LifecycleState `json:\"fromState\"`\n583:     ToState   LifecycleState `json:\"toState\"`\n584:     Timestamp time.Time      `json:\"timestamp\"`\n585:     Reason    string         `json:\"reason\"`\n586: }\n587: ```\n588: \n589: ---\n590: \n591: ## Integration with client-go\n592: \n593: | Component | Usage |\n594: |-----------|-------|\n595: | `dynamic.Interface` | Delete Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs |\n596: | `metav1.DeleteOptions` | Configure graceful period, propagation policy |\n597: | `informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory` | Watch for resource changes during deletion |\n598: \n599: ---\n600: \n601: ## Notes\n602: \n603: - Deletion is idempotent; deleting a non-existent sandbox returns 404, but force deleting returns 200 if already deleted\n604: - Graceful shutdown timeout can be customized per-request via query parameter or globally via environment variable\n605: - Background workers (idle detector, orphan cleaner) run independently and are resilient to individual operation failures\n606: - All K8s API errors are mapped to appropriate HTTP status codes following Kubernetes conventions\n607: - Store cleanup is attempted even if resource cleanup fails to prevent data inconsistency\n608: - Batch deletion processes sandboxes in parallel with a configurable concurrency limit (default: 10)\n\n(End of file - total 608 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"### DeleteSandboxRequest\n```go\ntype DeleteSandboxRequest struct {\n    SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n}\n```\n\n### DeleteSandboxResponse\n```go\ntype DeleteSandboxResponse struct {\n    SandboxID        string         `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SessionID        string         `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    Status           string         `json:\"status\"` // \"deleted\", \"terminating\", \"failed\"\n    DeletedAt        time.Time      `json:\"deletedAt,omitempty\"`\n    ResourcesCleaned []ResourceInfo `json:\"resourcesCleaned,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype ResourceInfo struct {\n    Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`\n    Name      string `json:\"name\"`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/c